Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. A method comprising: transmitting, using a searching device (112), a search query (300) to a search system (100) configured to generate search results (308) in response to a received search query (300); selecting, using the searching device (112), one of a plurality of viewing devices (114); receiving search results (308) from the search system (100) at the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) in response to transmitting the search query (300), wherein each search results (308) indicates a function for a computing device to perform; displaying the search results (308) on the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114); receiving a user selection of one of the search results (308) at the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114); and transmitting, using the one of the plurality of viewing devices (1 14), an indication of the user selection to a performing device (116, 538), wherein the performing device (116, 538) is configured to perform the function indicated by the one of the search results (308) in response to receiving the indication. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving a user selection of a viewing device (114) of the plurality of viewing devices (114) at the searching device (112), and selecting the viewing device (114) as the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the user selection. 3. The method of claim 2, further comprising displaying an indication of the viewing device (114) of the plurality of viewing devices (114) on the searching device (112), wherein receiving the user selection of the viewing device (114) comprises receiving a user selection of the indication at the searching device (112). 4. The method of claim 3, further comprising displaying an indication of each of one or more of the following on the searching device (112): a location of the viewing device (1 14) of the plurality of viewing devices (114); whether the viewing device (114) is available to display the search results (308); whether the viewing device (114) is capable of displaying the search results (308); whether the viewing device (114) is connected to the searching device (1 12) via a communication interface (106); whether the viewing device (114) has been previously connected to the searching device (112) via a communication interface (106); whether the viewing device (114) has been previously selected by the searching device (112); or how frequently the viewing device (114) has been previously selected by the searching device (112). 5. The method of claim 1, further comprising receiving an indication of one or more potential viewing devices (114) that include the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) from a user at the searching device (112), wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the indication. 6. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving location data (120) that indicates a location of each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114), and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the location data (120). 7. The method of claim 6, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the location data (120) comprises identifying a viewing device (114) of the plurality of viewing devices (114) that is located most proximate to the searching device (112) using the location data (120), and selecting the viewing device (114) as the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114). 8. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving availability data (122) that indicates whether each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114) is available to display the search results (308), and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the availability data (122). 9. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving compatibility data (124) that indicates whether each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114) is capable of displaying the search results (308), and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the compatibility data (124). 10. The method of claim 9, wherein the compatibility data (124) indicates one or more of a display technology, a display resolution, and a display size associated with each of the one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114), the method further comprising determining one or more of a display technology, a display resolution, and a display size associated with the search results (308), wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the compatibility data (124) comprises selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the compatibility data (124) and based on the determination. 11. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving connectivity data (126) that indicates whether each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114) is connected to the searching device (112) via a communication interface (106), and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the connectivity data (126). 12. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving historical connectivity data (126) that indicates whether each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114) has been previously connected to the searching device (112) via a communication interface (106), 

 and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the historical connectivity data (126). 13. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving previous selection data (128) that indicates whether each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114) has been previously selected by the searching device (112), and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the previous selection data (128). 14. The method of claim 1, wherein selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) comprises receiving previous selection data (128) that indicates how frequently each of one or more of the plurality of viewing devices (114) has been previously selected by the searching device (112), and selecting the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) based on the previous selection data (128). 15. The method of claim 1, wherein the one of the search results (308) includes an access mechanism (406), and wherein to perform the function indicated by the one of the search results (308), the performing device (116, 538) is configured to set an application (228, 234, 246, 248) into a state of the application (228, 234, 246, 248) using the access mechanism (406). 16. The method of claim 1, wherein to perform the function indicated by the one of the search results (308), the performing device (116, 538) is configured to: display an expanded version of the one of the search results (308) to a user; receive a selection of the expanded version from the user; and perform the function indicated by the one of the search results (308) in response to receiving the selection. 17. The method of claim 1, wherein the performing device (116, 538) and the searching device (112) are the same device. 18. The method of claim 1, wherein the performing device (116, 538) and the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) are the same device. 19. A system comprising: a searching device (112); a plurality of viewing devices (114); a performing device (116, 538); and a search system (100), wherein the search system (100) is configured to receive a search query (300) from the searching device (112) and transmit search results (308) that are responsive to the search query (300), wherein the searching device (112) is configured to select one of the plurality of viewing devices (114), wherein the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) is configured to receive the search results (308) from the search system (100), display the search results (308) to a user, receive a user selection of one of the search results (308) from the user, and transmit an indication of the user selection to the performing device (116, 538), and wherein the performing device (116, 538) is configured to perform a function indicated by the one of the search results (308) in response to receiving the indication. 20. A non-transitory computer-readable storage medium comprising instructions that cause one or more computing devices to: transmit, using a searching device (112), a search query (300) to a search system (100) configured to generate search results (308) in response to a received search query (300); select, using the searching device (112), one of a plurality of viewing devices (114); receive search results (308) from the search system (100) at the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114) in response to transmitting the search query (300), wherein each search results (308) indicates a function for a computing device to perform; display the search results (308) on the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114); 

 receive a user selection of one of the search results (308) at the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114); and transmit, using the one of the plurality of viewing devices (114), an indication of the user selection to a performing device (116, 538), wherein the performing device (116, 538) is configured to perform the function indicated by the one of the search results (308) in response to receiving the indication.
